<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontbureau/spira/">Spira</a>: very nice as well</li>
<li><a href="http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/linotype/itc-golden-cockerel/">Golden Cockerel</a>: my new favorite? It would be fitting if both my top fonts were by Eric Gill.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.identifont.com/show?1H2">Mrs Eaves</a>: This is definitely my favorite serif. It's well-built (with oldstyle figures, small caps (even petite caps!) and an elegant italic) but still has enough character to make it enjoyable. I haven't looked at pages of type set in it yet, so it might not work out, but I'm certainly attracted to it. I first saw it on the <a href="http://www.blindfaithcafe.com/">Blind Faith Caf&eacute;</a> menu (2002-12-23), and got its name thru <a href="http://www.myfonts.com/WhatTheFont/">WhatTheFont</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.myfonts.com/FontFamily26300.html">Electra LH</a> (<a href="http://www.myfonts.com/MoreLike?id=26300">more</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.myfonts.com/FontFamily4205.html">Minion</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.identifont.com/show?FK">Bembo</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.identifont.com/show?TI">Palatino</a> Roman / <a href="http://www.identifont.com/show?EK">Aldus</a> Roman</li>
<li><a href="http://www.identifont.com/show?2R2">Birka</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.identifont.com/show?M8">Georgia</a> (<a href="http://www.myfonts.com/FontFamily391.html">MyFonts</a>, <a href="http://www.users.bigpond.com/studiodata/verdana.htm">Mac/Win</a>, <a href="http://corefonts.sourceforge.net/">Linux</a>)
<li><a href="http://www.veer.com/results.asp?image=SHT0000018">Goodchild</a> (Jenson, Iowa...)</li>
</ul>
